        "description": {
            "value": "<p>You utter a liberating word of power that frees a creature. You suppress one of the following conditions of your choice: @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Confused]{Confused}, @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Frightened]{Frightened}, @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Grabbed]{Grabbed}, or @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Paralyzed]{Paralyzed}. The target isn't affected by the chosen condition, and if you suppress the Grabbed condition, the target automatically breaks free from any grab affecting it when you Cast the Spell.</p>\n<p>If you don't remove the effect that provided the condition, the condition returns after the spell ends. For example, if a spell was making the target Confused for 1 minute, word of freedom would let the target act normally for a round, but the Confused condition would return afterward.</p>"
